HEADWORD: Fluviatile
<hw>Flu"vi*a*tile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fluviatilis</ets>, fr. <ets>fluvius</ets> river: cf. F.
<ets>fluviatile</ets>.]</ety> <def>Belonging to rivers or streams;
existing in or about rivers; produced by river action; fluvial; <as>as,
<ex>fluviatile</ex> starta, plants</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Lyell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
